sentences.english: Heroin has been smuggled out by sea.
sentences.chinese: 海洛因已從海上偷運出境。

sentences.english: Tyson Foods was charged with smuggling illegal immigrants to work in meat packing plants.
sentences.chinese: 泰森食品公司被指控偷運非法移民在肉食包裝廠打工。

sentences.english: They tied her up,drugged her,and smuggled her across the border.
sentences.chinese: 他們把她捆牢了，使她失去知覺，並把她偷運過邊界。

sentences.english: Stol'n on his wing my three-and-twentieth year!
sentences.chinese: 它的翅膀上偷運着我的二十三歲。

sentences.english: They used to run firearms into neighbouring countries.
sentences.chinese: 他們過去經常偷運槍支到鄰近國家。

sentences.english: India seizes third shipment of tiger parts on way to China .
sentences.chinese: 印度捕獲第三隻偷運虎骨至中國的走私船。

sentences.english: The rockets were smuggled in through tunnels under the border with Egypt.
sentences.chinese: 火箭彈是通過和埃及邊界的地下隧道偷運進來的。

sentences.english: The company bootlegged corn whiskey during Prohibition.
sentences.chinese: 那家公司在禁酒期間偷運玉米威士忌。

sentences.english: People who smuggle contraband goods will be punished by the law.
sentences.chinese: 偷運違禁物品的行爲，要受到法律的制裁。
